  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points, with parameter sweeps covering viscosity, inlet velocity, and turbulence intensity. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; 7 were formally assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 are flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted pending remediation plan.",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
