      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "Computational velocity fields compared against particle image velocimetry measurements from the FDA benchmark study. Mean absolute error in axial velocity: 8.3%. The UQ campaign (Monte Carlo, 1200 samples) quantified combined uncertainty from inlet boundary conditions and fluid viscosity; sensitivity indices were computed internally and documented in the UQ report but are not linked as a structured sensitivity analysis object in this package."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index absolute value comparison",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 operating points. Predictions within 22% of measured values at 3 of 5 points; 2 outlier points exceed 35% deviation. Monte Carlo UQ showed 90th-percentile prediction interval spans factor of 2.1 for worst-case operating condition."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/grid-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid convergence index study — three mesh levels",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three mesh levels (2.1M, 8.4M, 33.6M cells). GCI for shear stress QoI: 4.7% on fine mesh. Discretization error assessed as Gradation 2 achieved against Gradation 4 required at MRL 5."
    }
  ],
